, United Kingdom","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Tower","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone who lived near a tower, usually a defensive fortification or watchtower, from Middle English, Old French <i>tūr</i> (from Latin <i>turris</i>).","English: occupational name for someone who dressed white leather, cured with alum rather than tanned with bark, from an agent derivative of Middle English <i>taw(en)</i> (Old English <i>tawian</i> ‘to prepare, make ready’).","Americanized form of German   Tauer  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Towers","meanings":["English:","variant of   Tower  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","habitational name for someone from Tours in Indre-et-Loire, northern France, so called from the Gaulish tribal name <i>Turones</i>, of uncertain etymology."]},{"name":"Tauer","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Alois, Erwin.","German (Silesia): habitational name from any of the places called Tauer or Thauer.","North German: occupational name for a tanner."]},{"name":"Toyer","meanings":["English: variant of   Tower  ."]},{"name":"Tuer","meanings":["English (northern): occupational name from Middle English <i>tewer(e)</i> ‘tawer’, an agent noun derived from <i>teuen</i> ‘to taw’ (Old English <i>tēwian</i>), denoting someone who prepared animal skins or hides for use by dressing, curing, or treating them. Compare   Tower  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Tower was born in 1290, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Peter Tower. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Thomas Tower."},"et":{"1290–":"1290–Surnud","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1310":"1310","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Thornock, Lincs, Eng.":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1290–":"1290–Kuollut","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","1310":"1310","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Thornock, Lincs, Eng.":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, England"},"fr":{"1290–":"1290–Décédé","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1290–Female":"1290–Décédée","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1260–Male":"1260–Décédé","1310":"1310","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Thornock, Lincs, Eng.":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Tower est né en 1290, à Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Peter Tower. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs. Thomas Tower."},"de":{"1290–":"1290–Verstorben","1290–Male":"1290–Verstorben","1290–Female":"1290–Verstorben","1310–Male":"1310–Verstorben","1260–Male":"1260–Verstorben","1310":"1310","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Thornock, Lincs, Eng.":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, England","lifeSummary":"Thomas Tower wurde 1290 in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, als Sohn von Peter Tower geboren. Er hatte mit Mrs. Thomas Tower mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1290–":"1290–Desede","1290–Male":"1290–Desede","1290–Female":"1290–Desede","